PART 3 — THE TWO BARS
🧼 Cleanliness (CL) — Your HP (0–100)
Increases ONLY from enemy food hits
Does NOT decay naturally
Healed by: Napkin (−25 CL), Sink (→ 0), certain self-consume recipes
80%+: Bathroom access unlocked. Player can still move and throw freely.
~95%: 0.75s warning slow + screen edge effect — telegraphs what's coming
100%: INSTANT debuff state. No grace period at 100%.
Sub-100% grace window: After any single hit of 40+ CL below 100%, player has 1.5s before consequences resolve — protects against rapid multi-hit combos
🍔 Fullness (FL) — Control / Penalty Resource (0–100)
FL is a control and penalty resource only — not a win condition
Increases from: food hits (+1 FL per raw/cold recipe hit, +2 FL per cooked recipe hit), eating buff recipes, looting trash cans
Increases from: getting hit by your own favourite thrown by an enemy (×2 FL spike)
Decays slowly over time on its own
10–20%: +10% player size, −10% movement speed
20–30%: +25% player size, −25% movement speed
80%+: Bathroom access unlocked. Player can still move and throw freely.
~95%: Same 0.75s warning applies
100%: INSTANT debuff state. No grace period at 100%.
Taking any damage: ALL active buff durations reduced by 15%
> **Design principle:** Cleanliness = survival. Fullness = control and pressure. These roles do not overlap.
💥 100% State (CL or FL) — LOCKED
When either bar hits 100%, the following triggers instantly with no grace period:
Effect	Detail
0.5s dramatic slow + sound cue	Cinematic moment — turns frustration into drama
Drops ALL inventory	Every ingredient, dish, and held item drops to floor
−30% movement speed	Applied immediately after drop
Still fully vulnerable	CL and FL damage lands normally — intentional humiliation
Can pick up items	Yes, but weight limit applies and pickup speed scales with overweight
Both bars at 100% simultaneously:
−60% movement speed (stacked −30% + −30%)
Both visuals stacked: maximum mess + maximum bloat
Needs 2 Potty Breaks to clear (Sink + Toilet)
> **No action locks.** No "can't throw" or "can't pick up" restrictions. The 0.5s cue, item drop, and speed debuff are the full punishment. Scrambling to recover at −30/−60% speed while being pelted is the intended experience.
