Revealing another player's allergy/favourite = 5 medals (tactical purchase, mid-match)
Reveal lasts the rest of the match once purchased
Available during all phases from Gathering onwards
12. Rematch vote
Simple majority threshold: 50% + 1 vote
30-second voting window
Eliminated/spectator players CAN vote — they participated in the match
Exactly tied vote = no rematch, lobby resets
Players who leave during vote count as "no"
13. Player disconnect mid-match
Their inventory drops to floor at their last known position (same as 100% state drop)
Their alliance auto-breaks with public Chompy announcement
Any sous-chef session they were part of — all ingredients return to respective owners
Their player slot opens for the next match
Eliminated players who reconnect can only spectate for remainder of match
14. Gathering and cooking during Food Fight — CONFIRMED OPEN
Store stays fully open all phases
All zones, checkout, and kitchen remain accessible during Food Fight
This is intentional — creates rich risk/reward decisions throughout the full match
Players who cook mid-fight gain ammo but sacrifice safety and mobility
This should be noted explicitly in the Rules tab
15. Scoring tie resolution
Tie on CL dealt AND points simultaneously → both players receive full medal value for that accolade
Last One Standing: cannot tie (someone always eliminated first, or Together winners are defined)
If timer expires with multiple survivors still alive → all surviving players share Last One Standing (all receive 60 medals)
16. Milk self-drink mechanic
Milk is the only raw ingredient with a defined self-use mechanic (besides Napkin)
Hold E on selected Milk = self-drink: −10 CL to yourself, 0.5s animation, interruptible
Throw Milk = weak wide hit (existing)
No cooking required for either use
Milk dual-use noted explicitly in CookbookBuilder ingredient card
17. Detection radius — precise definition
Detection radius = the size of your dot on OTHER players' minimaps
Normal dot size = 2 stud visual radius
Cart (+15%) = 2.3 stud dot
Solo player (−20%) = 1.6 stud dot
80%+ CL = 3.0 stud dot (visibly larger — enemies track you easier)
Cooking = your dot pulses to a 15-stud flash radius briefly — not a permanent size increase
18. Phase transition — player spawn and movement
Players spawn in car park during Prelobby — no forced movement at any time
When Gathering starts: store doors animate open, no teleport
Players walk in naturally under their own control
Zone suggestion markers appear on floor near each zone entrance as visual guides only
No forced routing, no teleportation, no movement locks at any phase transition
The only forced movement is walking to bathroom when at 100% (player controlled, just debuffed)
19. Scoring phase tracking
Points tracking begins at Gathering phase start
Scoreboard accessible via Tab from Gathering phase onwards
All accolades draw from full-match stats (Gathering through Food Fight)
Ingredient pickups during Gathering count for Resource Raider and points
Checkout purchases during any phase count for Super Shopper
20. Napkin edge cases
Interrupted at any point = NO heal, zero CL recovered
Cooldown starts on activation (not completion) — prevents spam-attempting
Can use Napkin while moving
Partial heals do not exist — all or nothing
Rationale: food hits are what interrupt it — you can't use a napkin to clean yourself while food is actively hitting you
