Scales give players a quick cost preview before committing to checkout. This is especially useful when:
A player picked up several expensive items and wants to confirm they have enough cash.
A player is deciding whether to drop a low-priority ingredient to afford a key one.
A player near the Bakery or Produce sections doesn't want to walk all the way to checkout just to check.
The Bakery and Produce scales encourage players to stay deeper in the store longer rather than clustering near checkout, which improves map flow.
