PART 32 — COOKING SYSTEM DETAIL (LOCKED)
> Confirmed during cooking design session, March 2026.
> All values simulation-verified against 3-minute Cooking phase + 6-minute Food Fight phase.
---
Overview
Cooking is a two-station process: Prep Table → Stovetop (for hot recipes), or Prep Table only (for cold/assembled recipes). Both stations lock to the active player and are exposed to combat interruption.
---
Prep Table — Recipe Assembly Minigame
Station Lock
Player approaches → slot locks to them instantly
Other players see the slot as occupied (visual indicator on prop)
Slot releases on: player departure, cook completion, or interruption
Maximum 1 player per slot at all times
Assembly Flow
A compact screen-space UI panel opens (centre-right, non-blocking)
Recipe selector at top: scrollable list filtered to valid recipes from current inventory. Shows name, ingredient list, CL value, and whether it requires a stovetop
Player selects a recipe → numbered ingredient slots appear below (2, 3, or 4 slots)
Player places each ingredient in order using the interact key — wrong ingredient flashes the slot red, no penalty beyond lost time
All slots filled → prep complete
Speed Bonus
A speed timer bar runs from the moment the first ingredient is placed
Fill all slots before the bar empties = +5% CL on final throw (stacks multiplicatively with all other bonuses)
The speed bonus window is generous — intended to reward focused play, not punish casual play
On speed success: "Perfect Prep!" visual flourish + audio cue, visible to nearby players
No mechanical effect beyond the 5% CL multiplier — no cook depth tier change
Cold / Prep-Only Recipes
Recipes that don't require a stovetop complete at the prep table
2-second pickup delay after final slot filled (plating moment), then immediately throwable
No stovetop step, no burn risk, no tending mechanic
Cook depth bonus (5/10/15%) does NOT apply to cold recipes — they deal base CL only
Speed bonus DOES apply to cold recipes
Cold recipes are intentionally lower damage but higher volume — a legitimate fast-cycle playstyle using cheaper, lower-CL ingredients
Interruption
Any single hit of 25+ CL while actively at the prep table drops the cook
All placed ingredients scatter as individual floor pickups within 10-stud radius
Slot unlocks immediately
No partial credit — assembly must restart from scratch
---
Stovetop — Ingredient Juggle Minigame
Station Lock
Same lock behaviour as prep table
Player places prepped bundle on stovetop → cook timer begins
Slot releases on: cook completion, player departure + burn expiry, or interruption
Cook Timers (by recipe complexity)
Complexity	Ingredients	Cook Time	Example
Simple	2	12s	Tomato Soup, Butter Chicken
Medium	3	20s	Saffron Rice, Callaloo
Complex	4+	30s	TrufflePasta, MDS
Vertical slice: flat 30s for all recipes. Tier system activates post-vertical-slice.
Tending Mechanic (Juggle)
While at the stovetop: 2–3 floating ingredient icons appear on screen, drifting slowly toward a red outer danger ring
Player taps interact to nudge icons back toward the safe green centre zone
Each nudge has a ~1s cooldown — rhythmic, not spam
Keeping all icons in the green zone at cook completion = +10% CL bonus on the final throw
Any icon that reaches the red outer ring = that ingredient's CL contribution is halved for this recipe (partial scorch — recoverable if tended back before timer ends)
Burn System (Leaving the Stovetop)
Player may leave at any time after placing the bundle
Icons drift 2× faster while unattended
Burn window (scaled by complexity):
Complexity	Burn Window
Simple (12s cook)	15s after departure
Medium (20s cook)	22s after departure
Complex (30s cook)	30s after departure
Burn window expires → burn modifier applied: recipe CL reduced by ×0.70
Burned recipe still completes and is throwable — burning is a quality hit, not a total loss
Returning to the stovetop before burn window expires cancels the burn and resumes normal drift speed
Interruption
Player present at stovetop: 25+ CL single hit drops the cook
Player away from stovetop: 40+ CL single hit drops the cook
On interruption: bundle and all ingredients scatter as individual floor pickups within 10-stud radius
Partial cook is lost — no carry-over progress, no partial state
Slot unlocks immediately
---
Full Multiplier Stack (Maximum Theoretical)
A 4-ingredient stovetop recipe, fast-prepped, fully tended, with no burn:
Modifier	Value
Cook depth (4+ ingredients)	×1.15
Tending bonus (all green at completion)	×1.10
Speed bonus (fast assembly)	×1.05
Combined	×1.3283 (≈ ×1.33)
This requires three simultaneous skill expressions and is the intended skill ceiling for cooking. Allergy, mark, favourite food, and alliance modifiers stack on top of this at throw time per existing rules.
---
Phase Simulation (Verified)
Cooking phase: 180s | Food Fight cooking window: 360s
Strategy	Cycle Time	Dishes/Phase	Relative CL Output
Cold spam (2s pickup)	~22s	~8 cooking / ~16 food fight	High volume, base CL only
Simple stovetop (12s)	~32s	~5 cooking	63% volume × 1.05 depth
Medium stovetop (20s)	~40s	~4 cooking	55% volume × 1.10 depth
Complex stovetop (30s)	~50s	~3 cooking	37% volume × 1.15+ depth
Key finding: Cold recipe spam is NOT a balance problem. It is a legitimate low-risk, low-reward playstyle. The balance is self-correcting through ingredient power — cold recipes use cheaper, lower base-CL ingredients. Stovetop recipes use expensive, high-CL ingredients (Wagyu, Truffle, Saffron). Both strategies are viable with different risk profiles.
Do not nerf cold recipe pickup time or add penalties to cold dishes. The current design is intentionally balanced.
