Zone Priority Rules
When a player occupies overlapping zones, the following priority order applies:
WC zones — always win. Bathroom immunity overrides everything.
Buffer zones — win over their adjacent gameplay zone (Produce/Bakery/Kitchen).
Kitchen — wins over Produce and Bakery at the deli border (Z≈100–152).
Produce / Bakery / Aisles / Freezer — peer priority, no overlap between these.
Checkout zones — win over TradeHub if overlapping.
CarPark / Stockroom — lowest priority, base fallback.
The Produce/Bakery overlap with Kitchen at the deli counter border (Z≈100–152, X=±180–300) is intentional. No prep tables or stovetops exist in this overlap area — Kitchen zone logic only fires on cooking station interaction, not on zone entry. No scripting conflict.
---
Dumpster Zone Handling
Dumpsters (`Dumpster_1_Body`, `Dumpster_2_Body`) are located at Z=315, outside the store in the back area. They are intentionally zone-less — the loot and interaction scripts find them by attribute (`IsTrashBin=true`), not by zone membership.
Dumpster trash mechanic (LOCKED):
Dumpsters are shared-inventory containers (`SharedInventory=true`)
Any player can deposit or retrieve items
Picking up from a dumpster triggers a CL hit (`CLOnPickup=true`) — reward for dumpster diving is risk
Max 8 items per dumpster (`MaxItems=8`)
Dumpsters do NOT reset between phases — items persist until picked up or match ends
Dumpster contents are visible to all players (shared inventory = public knowledge)
