PART 34 — BALANCE PATCH v1 (LOCKED)
> Applied after external systems audit, March 2026.
> Six targeted tweaks. No systems redesigned.
---
Changes Applied
1. Fullness Per Hit — Differentiated by Recipe Type
Old: +2 FL per hit (flat)
New: +1 FL per raw/cold recipe hit | +2 FL per cooked recipe hit
Rationale: Prevents fullness bars from escalating too fast under cold-recipe spam, while preserving the meaningful pressure of cooked recipes. Rewards cooking without punishing the cold-dish playstyle.
---
2. Minimum Movement Speed — Floor Clamped at 35%
New rule: Player movement speed can never fall below 35% of base speed regardless of stacking penalties.
Stacking scenario that triggered this: overweight (−25%) + dual 100% bars (−30% + −30%) = −85%, leaving players at ~15% speed which is effectively immobilised. 35% floor ensures players can always meaningfully reposition.
Applies to: CharacterController speed calculation. Clamp is applied after all modifiers are summed.
---
3. Dropped Item Protection — 1 Second Owner Lock on 100% Drop
New rule: When a player triggers the 100% state and drops their inventory, all dropped items are owner-locked for 1 second. Other players cannot pick them up during this window. After 1 second, items are free-for-all.
Rationale: Prevents instant gear transfer on 100% state which creates a snowball loop where the strongest player gets richer by targeting weakened players. The 1-second window is short enough to feel fair to attackers.
Implementation: Dropped parts get `OwnerLock=true` and `OwnerPlayer=userId` attributes on spawn. IngredientPickupServer checks these before allowing pickup.
---
4. Poke Deluxe CL Reduction
Old: 49 CL
New: 44 CL
Rationale: At 49 CL, Poke Deluxe (prep-only, raw) outperformed Lobster Bisque (45 CL, prep+stove) and Saffron Rice (44 CL, prep+stove). A prep-only recipe should not exceed or match stovetop equivalents in damage output. 44 CL keeps it competitive as the strongest cold recipe while maintaining the stovetop advantage.
---
5. Throw Cooldown Increased
Old: 0.4s
New: 0.8s
Rationale: At 0.4s cooldown, theoretical cold-recipe output reaches ~210 CL/minute of sustained throw DPS, which is too high. 0.8s halves the effective throw rate, makes combat more readable for all players, and preserves the cooking advantage without nerfing cold recipes directly.
Note: The rarity-scaled throw cooldown table (Common 0.8s base + wt modifier, Uncommon 0.4s etc.) remains unchanged — the 0.8s is the new Common baseline.
---
6. Maximum Bathroom Stay — 10 Seconds After Full Reset
New rule: Players may not remain in a bathroom indefinitely. After both CL and FL have been fully reset to 0, a 10-second timer begins. At expiry, the player is automatically exited from the bathroom (same as normal exit — 1.5s grace window applies).
Implementation note: The timer does NOT start on bathroom entry. It starts when both bars reach 0. A player who enters at 95% CL gets full healing time before the 10s window begins.
Rationale: Prevents stalling in bathroom to avoid combat. The bathroom is a recovery tool, not a permanent safe house.
---
Decisions NOT Changed
Golden Cart values (+40% speed, ×2 throw range): Left unchanged. The 20-second duration already constrains the buff window sufficiently. Nerfing the values would reduce the viral moment quality. Revisit after playtesting if match-deciding.
Alliance re-formation exploit: Not applicable to this design. Alliance bands cost $12 each with no refund, consumed regardless of outcome. The financial cost is the natural deterrent. No separate point-farming mechanism exists to exploit.
Cold recipe balance: Cold recipes are intentionally weaker (no cook depth bonus, no tending bonus) but faster. This is a deliberate playstyle choice, not a problem. Do not nerf cold recipes directly.
---
End of Part 34 — Balance Patch v1
